dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-availablein.name: availableIncomingBitrate
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-availablein.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats property availableIncomingBitrate returns a value indicative of the available inbound capacity of the network connection represented by the candidate pair. The higher the value, the more bandwidth you can assume is available for incoming data.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-availablein.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.availableIncomingBitrate

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-availableou.name: availableOutgoingBitrate
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-availableou.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats property availableOutgoingBitrate returns a value indicative of the available outbound capacity of the network connection represented by the candidate pair. The higher the value, the more bandwidth you can assume is available for outgoing data.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-availableou.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.availableOutgoingBitrate

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-bytesreceiv.name: bytesReceived
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-bytesreceiv.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats property bytesReceived indicates the total number of payload bytes—that is, bytes which aren't overhead such as headers or padding—that have been received to date on the connection described by the candidate pair.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-bytesreceiv.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.bytesReceived

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-bytessent.name: bytesSent
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-bytessent.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats property bytesSent indicates the total number of payload bytes—that is, bytes which aren't overhead such as headers or padding—that have been sent so far on the connection described by the candidate pair.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-bytessent.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.bytesSent

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-consentrequ.name: consentRequestsSent
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-consentrequ.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats property consentRequestsSent specifies the number of consent requests that have been sent by this peer to the remote peer on the connection described by the pair of candidates.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-consentrequ.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.consentRequestsSent

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-currentroun.name: currentRoundTripTime
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-currentroun.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats property currentRoundTripTime is a floating-point value indicating the number of seconds it takes for data to be sent by this peer to the remote peer and back over the connection described by this pair of ICE candidates.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-currentroun.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.currentRoundTripTime

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-lastpacketr.name: lastPacketReceivedTimestamp
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-lastpacketr.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats property lastPacketReceivedTimestamp indicates the time at which the connection described by the candidate pair last received a packet. STUN packets are not included.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-lastpacketr.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.lastPacketReceivedTimestamp

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-lastpackets.name: lastPacketSentTimestamp
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-lastpackets.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats property lastPacketSentTimestamp indicates the time at which the connection described by the candidate pair last sent a packet, not including STUN packets.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-lastpackets.title: RTCIceCandidateStats.lastPacketSentTimestamp

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-localcandid.name: localCandidateId
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-localcandid.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats property localCandidateId is a string that uniquely identifies the local ICE candidate which was analyzed to generate the RTCIceCandidateStats used to compute the statistics for this pair of candidates.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-localcandid.title: RTCIceCandidateStats.localCandidateId

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-nominated.name: nominated
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-nominated.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats property nominated specifies whether or not the candidate pair described by the underlying RTCIceCandidatePair has been nominated to be used as the configuration for the WebRTC connection.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-nominated.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.nominated

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-packetsrece.name: packetsReceived
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-packetsrece.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats dictionary's packetsReceived property indicates the total number of packets of any kind that have been received on the connection described by the pair of candidates.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-packetsrece.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.packetsReceived

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-packetssent.name: packetsSent
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-packetssent.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats dictionary's packetsSent property indicates the total number of packets which have been sent on the connection described by the pair of candidates.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-packetssent.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.packetsSent

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-remotecandi.name: remoteCandidateId
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-remotecandi.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats property remoteCandidateId is a string that uniquely identifies the remote ICE candidate which was analyzed to generate the RTCIceCandidateStats used to compute the statistics for this pair of candidates.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-remotecandi.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.remoteCandidateId

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-requestsrec.name: requestsReceived
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-requestsrec.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats dictionary's requestsReceived property indicates the total number of STUN connectivity check requests that have been received so far on the connection described by this pairing of candidates.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-requestsrec.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.requestsReceived

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-requestssen.name: requestsSent
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-requestssen.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats dictionary's requestsSent property indicates the total number of STUN connectivity check requests that have been sent so far on the connection described by this pair of candidates.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-requestssen.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.requestsSent

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-responsesre.name: responsesReceived
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-responsesre.summary: The responsesReceived property in the RTCIceCandidatePairStats dictionary indicates the total number of STUN connectivity check responses that have been received on the connection described by this pair of candidates.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-responsesre.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.responsesReceived

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-responsesse.name: responsesSent
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-responsesse.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats dictionary's responsesSent property indicates the total number of STUN connectivity check responses that have been sent so far on the connection described by this pair of candidates.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-responsesse.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.responsesSent

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-state.name: state
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-state.summary: The state property in a string that indicates the state of the check list of which the candidate pair is a member.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-state.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.state

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-totalroundt.name: totalRoundTripTime
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-totalroundt.summary: The RTCIceCandidatePairStats dictionary's totalRoundTripTime property is the total time that has elapsed between sending STUN requests and receiving the responses, for all such requests that have been made so far on the pair of candidates described by this RTCIceCandidatePairStats object. This value includes both connectivity check and consent check requests.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-totalroundt.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.totalRoundTripTime

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-transportid.name: transportId
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-transportid.summary: The transportId property uniquely identifies the RTCIceTransport that was inspected to obtain the transport-related statistics contained in the RTCIceCandidatePairStats object.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats-transportid.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats.transportId

dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats.name: RTCIceCandidatePairStats
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats.summary: The WebRTC RTCIceCandidatePairStats dictionary reports statistics which provide insight into the quality and performance of an RTCPeerConnection while connected and configured as described by the specified pair of ICE candidates.
dom-rtcicecandidatepairstats.title: RTCIceCandidatePairStats

dom-rtcicecandidatestats-address.name: address
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-address.summary: The address property of the RTCIceCandidateStats dictionary indicates the address of the ICE candidate. While it's preferred that the address be specified as an IPv4 or IPv6 numeric address, a fully-qualified domain name can be used as well.
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-address.title: RTCIceCandidateStats.address

dom-rtcicecandidatestats-candidatetype.name: candidateType
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-candidatetype.summary: The RTCIceCandidateStats interface's candidateType property is a string which indicates the type of ICE candidate the object represents.
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-candidatetype.title: RTCIceCandidateStats.candidateType

dom-rtcicecandidatestats-deleted.name: deleted
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-deleted.summary: The RTCIceCandidateStats dictionary's deleted property indicates whether or not the candidate has been deleted or released.
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-deleted.title: RTCIceCandidateStats.deleted

dom-rtcicecandidatestats-port.name: port
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-port.summary: The RTCIceCandidateStats dictionary's port property specifies the network port used by the candidate.
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-port.title: RTCIceCandidateStats.port

dom-rtcicecandidatestats-priority.name: priority
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-priority.summary: The RTCIceCandidateStats dictionary's priority property is a positive integer value indicating the priority (or desirability) of the described candidate.
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-priority.title: RTCIceCandidateStats.priority

dom-rtcicecandidatestats-protocol.name: protocol
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-protocol.summary: The RTCIceCandidateStats dictionary's protocol property specifies the protocol the specified candidate would use for communication with the remote peer.
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-protocol.title: RTCIceCandidateStats.protocol

dom-rtcicecandidatestats-relayprotocol.name: relayProtocol
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-relayprotocol.summary: The RTCIceCandidateStats dictionary's relayProtocol property specifies the protocol being used by a local ICE candidate to communicate with the TURN server.
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-relayprotocol.title: RTCIceCandidateStats.relayProtocol

dom-rtcicecandidatestats-transportid.name: transportId
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-transportid.summary: The RTCIceCandidateStats dictionary's transportId property is a string that uniquely identifies the transport that produced the RTCTransportStats from which information about this candidate was taken.
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-transportid.title: RTCIceCandidateStats.transportId

dom-rtcicecandidatestats-url.name: url
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-url.summary: The RTCIceCandidateStats dictionary's url property specifies the URL of the ICE server from which the described candidate was obtained. This property is only available for local candidates.
dom-rtcicecandidatestats-url.title: RTCIceCandidateStats.url

icecandidate-dict*.name: RTCIceCandidateStats
icecandidate-dict*.summary: The WebRTC API's RTCIceCandidateStats dictionary provides statistics related to an RTCIceCandidate.
icecandidate-dict*.title: RTCIceCandidateStats

dom-rtcremoteoutboundrtpstreamstats-loca.name: localId
dom-rtcremoteoutboundrtpstreamstats-loca.summary: The RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats dictionary's localId property is a string which can be used to identify the RTCInboundRtpStreamStats object whose remoteId matches this value.
dom-rtcremoteoutboundrtpstreamstats-loca.title: RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats.localId

dom-rtcremoteoutboundrtpstreamstats-remo.name: remoteTimestamp
dom-rtcremoteoutboundrtpstreamstats-remo.summary: The RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats property remoteTimestamp indicates the timestamp on the remote peer at which these statistics were sent. This differs from timestamp, which indicates the time at which the statistics were generated or received locally.
dom-rtcremoteoutboundrtpstreamstats-remo.title: RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats.remoteTimestamp

remoteoutboundrtpstats-dict*.name: RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats
remoteoutboundrtpstats-dict*.summary: The WebRTC statistics model's RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats dictionary extends the underlying RTCSentRtpStreamStats dictionary with properties measuring metrics specific to outgoing RTP streams.
remoteoutboundrtpstats-dict*.title: RTCRemoteOutboundRtpStreamStats

dom-rtcrtpstreamstats-codecid.name: codecId
dom-rtcrtpstreamstats-codecid.summary: The RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary's codecId property is a string which uniquely identifies the object that was inspected to produce the data in the RTCCodecStats for the RTP stream.
dom-rtcrtpstreamstats-codecid.title: RTCRtpStreamStats.codecId

dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-fircount.name: firCount
dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-fircount.summary: The firCount property of the RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary indicates the number of Full Intra Request (FIR) packets have been sent by the receiver to the sender.
dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-fircount.title: RTCRtpStreamStats.firCount

dom-rtcoutboundrtpstreamstats-fircount.name: firCount
dom-rtcoutboundrtpstreamstats-fircount.summary: The firCount property of the RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary indicates the number of Full Intra Request (FIR) packets have been sent by the receiver to the sender.
dom-rtcoutboundrtpstreamstats-fircount.title: RTCRtpStreamStats.firCount

dom-rtcrtpstreamstats-kind.name: kind
dom-rtcrtpstreamstats-kind.summary: The kind property of the RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary is a string indicating whether the described RTP stream contains audio or video media.
dom-rtcrtpstreamstats-kind.title: RTCRtpStreamStats.kind

dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-nackcount.name: nackCount
dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-nackcount.summary: The nackCount property of the RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary is a numeric value indicating the number of times the receiver sent a NACK packet to the sender.
dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-nackcount.title: RTCRtpStreamStats.nackCount

dom-rtcoutboundrtpstreamstats-nackcount.name: nackCount
dom-rtcoutboundrtpstreamstats-nackcount.summary: The nackCount property of the RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary is a numeric value indicating the number of times the receiver sent a NACK packet to the sender.
dom-rtcoutboundrtpstreamstats-nackcount.title: RTCRtpStreamStats.nackCount

dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-plicount.name: pliCount
dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-plicount.summary: The pliCount property of the RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary states the number of times the stream's receiving end sent a Picture Loss Indication (PLI) packet to the sender.
dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-plicount.title: RTCRtpStreamStats.pliCount

dom-rtcoutboundrtpstreamstats-plicount.name: pliCount
dom-rtcoutboundrtpstreamstats-plicount.summary: The pliCount property of the RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary states the number of times the stream's receiving end sent a Picture Loss Indication (PLI) packet to the sender.
dom-rtcoutboundrtpstreamstats-plicount.title: RTCRtpStreamStats.pliCount

dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-qpsum.name: qpSum
dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-qpsum.summary: The qpSum property of the RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary is a value generated by adding the Quantization Parameter (QP) values for every frame sent or received to date on the video track corresponding to this RTCRtpStreamStats object.
dom-rtcinboundrtpstreamstats-qpsum.title: RTCRtpStreamStats.qpSum

dom-rtcoutboundrtpstreamstats-qpsum.name: qpSum
dom-rtcoutboundrtpstreamstats-qpsum.summary: The qpSum property of the RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary is a value generated by adding the Quantization Parameter (QP) values for every frame sent or received to date on the video track corresponding to this RTCRtpStreamStats object.
dom-rtcoutboundrtpstreamstats-qpsum.title: RTCRtpStreamStats.qpSum

dom-rtcrtpstreamstats-ssrc.name: ssrc
dom-rtcrtpstreamstats-ssrc.summary: The RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary's ssrc property provides the Synchronization Source (SSRC), an integer which uniquely identifies the source of the RTP packets whose statistics are covered by the RTCStatsReport that includes this RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary.
dom-rtcrtpstreamstats-ssrc.title: RTCRtpStreamStats.ssrc

dom-rtcrtpstreamstats-transportid.name: transportId
dom-rtcrtpstreamstats-transportid.summary: The RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary's transportId property is a string which uniquely identifies the object from which the statistics contained in the RTCTransportStats properties in the RTCStatsReport.
dom-rtcrtpstreamstats-transportid.title: RTCRtpStreamStats.transportId

streamstats-dict*.name: RTCRtpStreamStats
streamstats-dict*.summary: The RTCRtpStreamStats dictionary is returned by the RTCPeerConnection.getStats(), RTCRtpSender.getStats(), and RTCRtpReceiver.getStats() methods to provide detailed statistics about WebRTC connectivity.
streamstats-dict*.title: RTCRtpStreamStats
